<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-238-656  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 238 656.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Design  March 1 1990 v29 n5 p82(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>VHDL and simulation accelerators: key to high-gate-count ASICdesign. (VHSIC Hardware Description Language, Application-SpecificIntegrated Circuit)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Saxe, Tim.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The number of ASIC design tool suppliers who have come out insupport of VHDL, coupled with the Department of Defense mandatefor VHDL, make it a given that VHDL will become the standardhardware description language for ASIC design.andP;  The complexity ofVHDL will make gate-level simulation slow, calling foracceleration support to become an integral part of designmethodology.andP;  This is necessary to keep the development cyclewithin acceptable time limits.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Application-Specific Integrated CircuitsHardware Description Languagesm SimulationProduct DevelopmentCircuit Design.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>